# Trivy vulnerability ignore list.
#
# Policy: the HIGH+CRITICAL gate in .github/workflows/build-and-push.yml stays
# active for every package. Entries here are ONLY for HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs whose
# vulnerable code is vendored inside an upstream package we already track at its
# latest release, so there is no version to bump to until upstream reships. Each
# entry names where the code lives and a revisit date. Remove an entry as soon
# as a fixed upstream release is available.

# --- jackson-databind, vendored in Ray's ray_dist.jar --------------------------
# Present in the latest Ray (2.56.0, 2026-06-29 — the newest release that exists;
# api-gateway + generation-worker images). jackson-databind 2.18.6 -> fix 2.18.8.
# Not reachable via our Python dependency graph; only Ray reshipping the jar
# clears it. Revisit 2026-08-01.
CVE-2026-54512
CVE-2026-54513

# --- picomatch + sigstore, vendored in Next.js dist/compiled -------------------
# Present in the latest stable Next.js (16.2.10; web image) under
# next/dist/compiled/. picomatch 4.0.3 -> fix 4.0.4 (ReDoS); sigstore 3.1.0 ->
# fix 4.1.1. Next.js bundles its own copies, so a pnpm override cannot reach
# them; only a Next.js release refreshing its vendored deps clears these.
# Revisit 2026-08-01.
CVE-2026-33671
CVE-2026-48815
